OL,3,CAnalysis of the Spring Statement from
OL,4,CITV News experts
OL,6,FWelfare spending as a share of Gross
OL,7,FDomestic Product (GDP) will fall
OL,8,Fbetween 2026-27 and the end of the
OL,9,Fforecast. The Chancellor confirmed
OL,10,Fthat the package announced last week,
OL,11,Fwith changes to Personal Independence
OL,12,FPayment (PIP) and Universal Credit,
OL,13,Fwill go ahead. But, there was a
OL,14,Ffurther #500 million worth of cuts.
OL,16,FThe OBR has calculated #3.4 billion
OL,17,Fworth of savings, not the #5 billion
OL,18,Fthe Government initially stated it was.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
